# 🧠 AI Center System — Implementation Plan

> **Goal**: Build a dedicated AI Center (مركز الذكاء الاصطناعي) inside the Widad platform, integrating 3 ML prediction models (GDM, Preeclampsia, Preterm Birth) deployed on Hugging Face Spaces with the platform's patient data, doctor views, and admin analytics.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Schema Migration Strategy**: The existing prediction tables (`gestational_diabetes_predictions`, `preeclampsia_predictions`, `preterm_birth_predictions`) have fields that DON'T match the actual HF Space APIs. For example, the GDM table has `fasting_glucose`, `hba1c`, `random_glucose` — but the actual GDM model uses **zero lab tests**. The plan uses **new ALTER TABLE migrations** to add the correct fields and keep existing columns nullable for backward compatibility, rather than dropping+recreating tables.

> [!WARNING]
> **Hugging Face API Dependency**: All 3 models are hosted on HF Spaces which can go to sleep after inactivity. The first request may take 30-60 seconds to wake up. The service layer includes retry + timeout handling for this.

---

## Phase 1: Backend — Model & Schema Alignment

Align existing DB tables and Eloquent models with the actual HF Space API schemas documented in [ai_models_report.md](file:///d:/Final_Project_Implementation/Final_Project_Artificial_Intelligence_Ideas/ai_models_report.md).

---

### 1.1 Migrations

#### [NEW] `align_gdm_predictions_with_api.php`
**Path**: `database/migrations/2026_06_18_000001_align_gdm_predictions_with_api.php`

Add GDM API-aligned columns. The actual API accepts 11 fields (age, height_cm, weight_kg, no_of_pregnancy, family_history, pcos, sedentary_lifestyle, prediabetes, unexplained_prenatal_loss, large_child_or_birth_default, gestation_in_previous_pregnancy) and returns risk_probability, risk_category, final_risk, guardrail_applied, recommendation_en, recommendation_ar, top_factors, bmi_computed.

Changes:
- Add new columns: `height_cm`, `weight_kg`, `bmi_computed`, `no_of_pregnancy`, `sedentary_lifestyle`, `prediabetes`, `unexplained_prenatal_loss`, `large_child_or_birth_default`, `gestation_in_previous_pregnancy`, `risk_probability`, `risk_category`, `final_risk`, `guardrail_applied`, `recommendation_en`, `recommendation_ar`, `top_factors`
- Make old lab columns nullable if not already: `fasting_glucose`, `random_glucose`, `hba1c`, `weight_gain`, `ethnicity`, `pre_pregnancy_bmi`, `current_bmi`
- Make `model_version`, `algorithm_used`, `ai_analysis` nullable (will be populated from API)

#### [NEW] `align_preeclampsia_predictions_with_api.php`
**Path**: `database/migrations/2026_06_18_000002_align_preeclampsia_predictions_with_api.php`

Add PE API-aligned columns. The actual API accepts 11 fields (gravida, parity, gest_age, age, bmi, diabetes, htn, sysbp, diabp, hb, proteinuria) and returns prediction, probability, risk_status.

Changes:
- Add new columns: `gravida`, `parity`, `gest_age`, `hb`, `htn`, `proteinuria`, `prediction_class`, `probability`, `risk_status`, `input_echo`
- Rename existing: keep `systolic_bp`→maps from `sysbp`, `diastolic_bp`→maps from `diabp`

#### [NEW] `align_preterm_predictions_with_api.php`
**Path**: `database/migrations/2026_06_18_000003_align_preterm_predictions_with_api.php`

Add PTB API-aligned columns. The actual API accepts 10 fields (Age, Systolic BP, Diastolic, BS, BMI, Previous Complications, Preexisting Diabetes, Gestational Diabetes, Mental Health, Heart Rate) and returns prediction, risk_label, probability_high.

Changes:
- Add new columns: [bs](file:///d:/Final_Project_Implementation/Final_Project_Front_And_Back/Back-end/app/Models/User.php#166-170) (blood sugar), `heart_rate`, `previous_complications`, `preexisting_diabetes`, `gestational_diabetes`, `mental_health`, `prediction_class`, `risk_label`, `probability_high`, `api_note`
- Make stage-2 diagnostic columns nullable: `cervical_length`, `cervical_insufficiency`, `uterine_abnormalities`, `placental_issues`, `infection`, `multiple_pregnancy`, `preeclampsia_present`, `gestational_diabetes_present`

